comments.body:
Successfully Implemented versioning for **unprotected branches**, need to clean up workflows and commits.
need to figure out how to do this for protected branches

Latest updates:

Over the last 4 weeks I've been working on automations to get tokens that allow pushing to protected branches. 

2 tokens from different "users" are needed to create and approve a PR. 

1.  Token 1 generates a PR #X from `branch A` into `main` and versions the app, pushes code to #X
2. Token 2 Approves
3. Either token merges 

[@Zwiqler94/GH-Actions](https://www.GitHub.com/zwiqler94/gh-actions) abstracts this away.
It's taken forever but versioning is complete with the caveat that some language needs updates!!
